To invert 
A = \begin{pmatrix}-0.2 & 1.4\\[6pt]1.2 & -0.4\end{pmatrix}

1.  Compute the determinant  
   det A = (−0.2)(−0.4) − (1.4)(1.2)  
         = 0.08 − 1.68  
         = −1.6  

2.  Use the formula for a 2×2 inverse:  
   A^{-1} = \frac{1}{\det A}\begin{pmatrix}d & –b\\[3pt]–c & a\end{pmatrix}  
   Here a = −0.2, b = 1.4, c = 1.2, d = −0.4, so  

   A^{-1} = \frac{1}{−1.6}\begin{pmatrix}−0.4 & −1.4\\[3pt]−1.2 & −0.2\end{pmatrix}  
          = \begin{pmatrix}0.25 & 0.875\\[3pt]0.75 & 0.125\end{pmatrix}  

   (You can check by multiplying A·A^{-1} = I_2.)
